		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I don't have a DVD writer :P I use Nero for my burning needs <3.<br />
<br />
When I was researching about the DMA, I read that Windows will bump the controller down to PIO when you have hit a certain number of CRC errors. That would make sense since I had drive booting errors last week. I ended up booting from a WD diagnostics floppy and following the instructions they gave me to create a new boot configuration. It worked, and this problem came up shortly after.<br />
<br />
Loaded EQ and there's no frame lag. Thanks again Sneg!</div>
	</td>
